            <section id="overview">
                <div class="overview-header">
                    <h2 class="section-title">Overview</h2>
                    <p class="date-updated">Dec 29, 2023</p>
                </div>
                <p>La Mesa Ecopark is a sprawling urban park located in Quezon City, Metro Manila. It offers a natural sanctuary with lush forests, clean air, and a variety of recreational activities. The park is a vital part of the La Mesa Watershed, providing water supply and serving as a green lung for the city. It's perfect for nature lovers, families, and anyone looking to escape the hustle and bustle of urban life.</p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h3 class="section-title">Highlights</h3>
                <ul class="highlights-list">
                    <li>Beautiful nature trails surrounded by lush greenery and diverse wildlife</li>
                    <li>Family-friendly picnic areas and playgrounds for outdoor relaxation and fun</li>
                    <li>Eco-museum and orchidarium showcasing the region's rich biodiversity</li>
                    <li>Fishing lagoon and boating activities available for visitors</li>
                    <li>A peaceful urban escape promoting environmental awareness and conservation</li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h3 class="section-title">Activities</h3>
                <div class="activities-grid">
                    <div class="activity-card">
                        <div class="activity-image-wrapper">
                            <img src="~/Content/images/lamesa-biking.jpg" alt="Biking and Hiking Trails" class="activity-image" />
                        </div>
                        <div class="activity-info">
                            <strong class="activity-name">Biking / Hiking</strong>
                            <small class="activity-price">₱50 (Biking Fee)</small>
                            <p class="activity-description">Explore the scenic, winding trails through the park's lush forest. Great for exercise and nature viewing. Bike rentals are available.</p>
                            <a href="#" class="activity-details-link">Read more →</a>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="activity-card">
                        <div class="activity-image-wrapper">
                            <img src="~/Content/images/lamesa-boating.jpg" alt="Boating and Fishing Lagoon" class="activity-image" />
                        </div>
                        <div class="activity-info">
                            <strong class="activity-name">Boating / Fishing</strong>
                            <small class="activity-price">₱100 (Boating/hr)</small>
                            <p class="activity-description">Rent a boat and paddle around the tranquil lagoon or try your hand at catch-and-release fishing in the serene waters.</p>
